@startuml Qsix_Training_Phase_Timeline
title Q6 Training Phase Timeline and Research Evolution

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam activity {
  BackgroundColor White
  BorderColor Black
  ArrowColor Black
}

start

:v1 / Phase 1\nSingle-agent Krishna vs scripted Hunter;
note right
  Question:
  Can DQN learn the game at all?

  Result:
  Yes. Strong performance vs scripted
  and progressive Hunters.
end note

:CNN + Double DQN + Dueling\n6-channel grid encoding;

:v2/v3 / Phase 2\nSelf-play begins;
note right
  Hunter becomes a learned DQN agent.
  Training alternates between:
  - joint latest-vs-latest episodes
  - FSP episodes vs frozen snapshots
end note

:Critical bug fixes\nEpsilon decay and collision handling;

:v4 / Phase 2 hardened\nFull FIFO opponent pool;
note right
  Finding:
  More training did not solve collection.

  Failure:
  Bimodal collapse:
  Krishna either evades forever or dies.
end note

if (Why did collection collapse?) then (Reward incentives)
  :Collection attempt becomes negative EV\nagainst hardened Hunters;
else (Network capacity)
  :Single head suffers gradient conflict\ncollect vs evade;
endif

:v5 / Phase 3\nGOP + CHER + hierarchical pool;
note right
  GOP:
  Evade head + collect head + learned gate.

  CHER:
  Inject safe-collection counterfactuals.

  Hierarchical pool:
  Preserve easy opponents for practice.
end note

:Result\nMore pellet contact, still rare wins;
note right
  Current status:
  Useful research prototype.
  Architecture promising.
  Incentive problem unresolved.
end note

:v6 planned\nReward reshaping + curriculum +\nCHER dependency reduction;

stop
@enduml

